lties and presenting alternate theoretical interpretations that alleviate this incompatibility, Massimo Pigliucci and Jonathan Kaplan intertwine scientific and philosophical analysis to produce a coherent picture of evolutionary biology. Innovative and controversial, Making Sense of Evolution encourages further development of the Modern Synthesis and outlines what might be necessary for the continued refinement of this evolving field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEvolution (Biology). 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  abiology, life sciences, evolution, evolutionary studies, adaptation, philosophy of science, species, history, theory, interpretation, experimental methods, methodology, definitions, conceptual difficulties, theoretical interpretations, philosophical analysis, scientific thought, academic writing, coherent picture, innovative, controversial, modern synthesis, adaptive landscape, quantitative genetics, natural selection, population dynamics.1 aKaplan, Jonathan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022666836940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226668352423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226668352/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles